@bluesky Smart approach, but re-inventing the wheel &amp; missing a critical component: key rotation.

Key Event Receipt Infrastructure (KERI) is an IETF internet draft protocol (not platform) that addresses rotation, delegation, &amp; revocation, w/ multi-sig.

https://t.co/nRgXlTGC8G

@arcalinea Great piece. You've just described the need for Key Event Receipt Infrastructure (KERI), which is based on self-certifying identifiers and takes your concepts even further.

Red pill moment here: https://t.co/8ZvKdHgdB3

@SamuelMSmith #KERI #verifiablecredentials #SSI

@0ceans404 California DMV is working on this, @nikil just mentioned it to our team today!

Also @heirloom_io is building W3C compliant tech that will help make this a reality not only for drivers licenses but for all other types of licenses and credentials 

Can’t wait for this future 🤩

Polygon DID is the future of online identities that supports the exchange of verifiable credentials secured by cryptographic proofs and also supports the W3C open-source identity standard.
